<P><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">What if they can't decide who =
should have the vest, and both</FONT></U><U> <FONT SIZE=3D2 =
FACE=3D"Arial">drown</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">? Well, =
they are innocent, and stupid, too.</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 =
FACE=3D"Arial"></FONT></U><U> </U>
</P>

<P><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">I might need</FONT></U><U> <FONT =
SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">to use more such examples to better describe =
the multidimensional shape that is the concept of innocence =
but</FONT></U><U> <FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">I hope you are getting =
a flavor for it. It does imply nonviolence, =
responsibility</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial"> for =
yourself, caring for other</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 =
FACE=3D"Arial">s, and other elements.</FONT></U></P>

<P><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">Let me</FONT></U><U> <FONT SIZE=3D2 =
FACE=3D"Arial">reiterate</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial"> my =
moral axioms:</FONT></U>
</P>

<P><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">1 Innocent life wish may not be =
thwarted</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">.</FONT></U>
<BR><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">2 Truth may not be =
denied</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial"> except to =
serve</FONT></U><U> <FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">1</FONT></U><U></U>
<BR><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">3 Freedom may not be =
infringed</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">, except to serve =
1 and 2</FONT></U><U></U>
</P>

<P><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">Practical applications of these =
axioms yield in my mind</FONT></U><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial"> a =
system resembling a soft-core form of libertarianism.</FONT></U><U></U>
</P>

<P><U><FONT SIZE=3D2 FACE=3D"Arial">Rafal</FONT></U>
